        <p class="spatial-intro">
        Where exactly were these high-FARC municipalities? 
        The maps below show the geographic concentration: 
        the Amazon region ‚Äî<strong>Caquet√°, Guaviare, Meta, Putumayo</strong>‚Äî and 
        the Pacific coast. These regions share common characteristics: 
        high forest cover, weak historical state presence, limited infrastructure, 
        and economies linked to coca cultivation and cattle ranching.
    </p>
    <p class="spatial-instruction">
        <em>Use the sliders to observe the transition. FARC data ends in 2018 (post-demobilization), 
        while deforestation data extends to 2024, showing the lasting environmental impact produced by governance vacuums.</em>
