<!-- Territorial Reconfiguration -->
    

<section class="territorial-section" id="territorial">
    <div class="territorial-container">
        <!-- Text left -->
        <div class="territorial-text">
            <div class="section-label">Territorial Reconfiguration</div>
            
            <p class="territorial-intro">
                FARC's withdrawal did not create empty territory‚Äîit triggered a violent 
                competition for control. <strong>Dissident FARC factions</strong>, the 
                <strong>ELN guerrilla</strong>, and criminal organizations like the 
                <strong>Clan del Golfo</strong> rapidly moved into former FARC strongholds, 
                seeking access to coca cultivation routes, illegal mining, and extortion networks.
            </p>
            
            <p class="territorial-detail">
                Unlike FARC's relatively stable territorial governance, these new actors 
                operate with shorter time horizons and less interest in forest preservation. 
                The result: accelerated deforestation as land is cleared for cattle ranching 
                (land laundering) and coca expansion.
            </p>
            
            <p class="territorial-instruction">
                <em>Select an armed group and use the slider to track their geographic presence over time.</em>
            </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Chart right -->
        <div class="territorial-chart">
            <div id="chart-perpetrators"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>



<!-- Predictors Section -->
<section class="predictors-section" id="predictors">
    <div class="predictors-container">
        <!-- Text left -->
        <div class="predictors-text">
            <div class="section-label">Predictors of Deforestation</div>
            
            <p>
                To quantify the relationship between armed group presence and forest loss, 
                we estimated an OLS regression model predicting the <strong>change in deforestation</strong> 
                (post-2016 minus pre-2016) for each municipality.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                Municipalities with higher <strong>historical FARC presence</strong> (+180 ha) 
                and active <strong>FARC dissident factions</strong> (+91 ha) experienced 
                significantly greater increases in deforestation after the Peace Agreement.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                Interestingly, <strong>ELN presence</strong> is associated with <em>less</em> 
                deforestation change (-44 ha). This may reflect that ELN operates primarily 
                in mountainous and border regions with lower forest cover, rather than in 
                the Amazon and Orinoqu√≠a where deforestation is concentrated.
            </p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Chart right -->
        <div class="predictors-chart">
            <div id="chart-coefficients"></div>
            <div class="chart-legend">
                <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot sig"></span> Significant (p&lt;0.05)</span>
                <span class="legend-item"><span class="dot nosig"></span> Not significant</span>
            </div>
            <div class="chart-stats">R¬≤ = 17.3% | n = 1,032 municipalities</div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

